	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=30945"><span id="Scholar">jcpeery</span></a><br /><b><span id="Scholar">Scholar</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">31 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.52]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>The Grimlings had the owlbear caves on Veeshan last night.&nbsp;&nbsp;This spawn is in the far left hand room in the owlbear caves.  It's ph is a grimling guard at the back of the room.  Next to him is a Grimling manacrafter.  Both of them are exactly 10 minute spawns.  I killed the manacrafter first and then the guard.  This gave me a heads up each time the guard/Gleeknot was gonna spawn.  <br/><br/>I camped it for 2-3 hours.  Usually it alternated between Gleeknot and ph, but at least once there were 3 ph's in a row.  He dropped the hat 3x before dropping the belt.<br/><br/>I am a 46 pally and everything in the room was green except Gleeknot who was light blue.  However, he hits hard and fast and routinely took me to around 2 bubbles of health.  The greenies did not aggro unless I got very close to them and I never had any adds when fighting Gleeknot.<br/><br/>During the down time, you can take out quite a few of the green mobs and collect runes, weapons and the rare gems for sale later.<br/><br/>Good Luck</p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />Fenadin, Yazook and Fastolph of the Veeshan Server</td></tr>
